\______ Informations __________________________________________________________



\______ Installation __________________________________________________________

LINUX		To install `MDMA`, simply run `sudo ./INSTALL`. This script will
			check dependences before making the program.

			In case of error please refer to the dependences paragraph

MAC			.

WINDOWS		.

\______ Dependences ___________________________________________________________

[UBUNTU / DEBIAN]

opencv_core :
	install package libopencv-core-dev

opencv_highgui :
	install package libopencv-highgui-dev

open_imgproc :
	install package libopencv-imgproc-dev

asound :
	install package libasound2-dev

qmake :
	install package qt4-qmake


[...]


\______ Contact _______________________________________________________________

If you have any question or issue installing/using this software, please
contact us at `mdma@ens-lyon.fr`.

\______ Changelog _____________________________________________________________

v0.1.0 alpha	Full fonctionality including mouse and hand tracking. It is now
				possible to select which data changes when moving fadder.
				Configuration files are now signed with the version number to
				avoid conficts.

v0.0.0			Basic configuration editing, including load and save functions.
				Camera selection and flipping.

